Peugeot’s Slovak Plant Suspends Work on Disruption of Supplies

-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 
2011-09-14T13:25:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/peugeot-s-slovak-plant-suspends-work-on-disruption-of-supplies.html
PSA Peugeot Citroen’s Slovak
factory had to suspend production because of disrupted parts
deliveries from an unspecified supplier, the company said today.  Lines at the factory in Trnava, western Slovakia, were
halted on Sept. 9 and the suspension will last at least until
Sept. 16, Ivana Pavelkova, a spokeswoman for the Slovak unit,
said in a phone interview today,  The factory assembles Peugeot 207 cars as well as the
Citroen-brand C3 Picasso model. Last year, it produced about
186,000 vehicles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  